{
  "text": ". For a yellow droplet with diameter d \u00bc 2.2 mm [13], a peak absorption coefficient of 5.2 mm 21 follows. We have investigated whether such huge values can have consequences for the refractive index by considering the absorption spectra of four principal carotenoids identified from measured transmittance spectra as well as from chromatography of retinal extracts [CITATION_1] . Figure 2a shows the carotenoid absorption spectra, assuming a medium with peak absorption coefficient 1 mm",
